                            <comment id="466331" author="JIRAUSER18433" created="Tue, 5 Aug 2025 21:36:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Lustre retries establish a new connection. There are LNet retries, but the timeout is short (180 seconds maybe?). So LNet would give up during a longer downtime.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We&apos;ve seen cases where socklnd won&apos;t reconnect correctly after a service interruption. It&apos;ll get stuck in a loop of attempting to connect indefinitely. It&apos;s better to destroy all of this old connection state and start fresh. Try to establish a connect to send an LNet message - if that fails, let the upper layers decide what they want to do. If LNet or Lustre want to keep trying, let them. But don&apos;t loop in the LND forever.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="466321" author="adilger" created="Tue, 5 Aug 2025 19:53:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;What happens here if, say, a server goes down for an hour or a day and is then restored to service?  Will LNet still reconnect, or will Lustre-level retries establish a new connection?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
